laboratory_examinations.findings: Negative for Neisseria Gonorrhoeae by PCR.

The appendix demonstrates circumferential wall thickness (2 mm) and measures up to 9 mm in maximal diameter. There is a dilated and non-compressible distal blind-ending tubular structure with internal shadowing focus within, likely representing an inflamed appendix with an appendicolith. No periappendiceal/pericecal fluid is noted.
